STATE v. MRS. T. E. McAFEE. (Filed 19 March, 1930.)

See same case next preceding.

*510 Attorney-General Brummitt and Assistant Attorney-General Nash for the State. 0. N. Allen for defendant. Adams, J.

Tbe disposition of the defendant’s appeal is controlled by the opinion in the preceding case—S. v. Mrs. T. E. McAfee, ante, 507.

Judgment affirmed.
